=Description=

"Michael Zimmer is an Assistant Professor in the School of Information Studies at UWM.  He writes about information privacy on his website.  He explains to Lake Effect’s Bonnie North that one of the great challenges is to balance the speed and size of our internet tools, and the convenience they provide, with the erosion of our personal privacy. "
